==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Requin
<hw>Re"quin</hw> <pr>(r?"kw?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>reqiem</ets> a Mass sung for the dead. See <er>Requiem</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The man-eater, or white shark (<spn>Carcharodon
carcharias</spn>); -- so called on account of its causing
<xex>requiems</xex> to be sung.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Requirable</ent>⟦br⟧
